\": 30953, \"to\": 31067, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There was also special praise for the 45,000 volunteers who assisted during the Games, which began with a rain-soaked opening ceremony along the Seine on 26 July.As well as reflecting on the Olympics in Paris, the closing ceremony provided a showcase for Los Angeles, which will host the Games for a third time in 2028.R&B artist H.E.R.\", \"from\": 31067, \"to\": 31404, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 31213, \"end\": 31218, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999601211823673, \"rank\": 3.987747989151786e-05, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 31271, \"end\": 31276, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.556120703327853e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 31323, \"end\": 31334, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.956721663598194e-14, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 31398, \"end\": 31404, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/H.E.R.\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8298089014042313e-35, \"text\": \"H.E.R.\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/H.E.R.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/H.E.R.\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"performed the American national anthem inside Stade de France before viewers were transported to LA.Mountain biker Kate Courtney, track and field legend Michael Johnson and skateboarder Jagger Eaton took the Olympic flag on a tour of the city - visiting sites such as the Los Angeles Memorial Coliseum and Venice Beach - while Cruise was pictured in front of the iconic Hollywood sign, complete with Olympic rings.Rapper Snoop Dogg, who has been working as a special correspondent for American television network NBC during Paris 2024, performed alongside Dr Dre as part of a memorable finale that whetted the appetite for four years' time.00votesArticle Rating  He continued: \\\"During all this time, you lived peacefully together under one roof in the Olympic Village.\", \"from\": 31405, \"to\": 32173, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 31419, \"end\": 31443, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Star-Spangled_Banner\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"American national anthem\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Star-Spangled_Banner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Star-Spangled_Banner\"}, {\"begin\": 31451, \"end\": 31466, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stade de France\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}, {\"begin\": 31520, \"end\": 31533, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Courtney_(cyclist)\", \"score\": 0.9999981956923782, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kate Courtney\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Courtney_(cyclist)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Courtney_(cyclist)\"}, {\"begin\": 31558, \"end\": 31573, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Johnson_(sprinter)\", \"score\": 0.6562406956374156, \"rank\": 0.2753288987434648, \"text\": \"Michael Johnson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Johnson_(sprinter)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Johnson_(sprinter)\"}, {\"begin\": 31591, \"end\": 31603, \"title\": \"http://